description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit Band 5 Registered nurses within the Acute Admissions Unit (AAU) in Bluebell ward to join a team of nurses working within the Acute Medicine Division, focusing on the acute patients care, supporting early discharges and providing high quality compassionate care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have proven clinical skills, possess a professional nursing attitude to fill the role of Registered Nurse. You must also demonstrate critical thinking in the clinical decision-making process and display professionalism. The successful candidates will be highly motivated and possess good communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We support applications from newly qualified, experienced and return to practice nurses alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for candidates who share our passion in nursing, working closely with all members of the multidisciplinary team to ensure that a quality service and patient focused care are delivered at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Still not sure? Why not come and take a look around and meet the team and its ward manager. We are friendly, supportive, enthusiastic team, always seeking to develop our service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an employer of nearly 5,000 staff, West Hertfordshire Hospitals NHS Trust is the place to be. Having have been shortlisted over the last three years for 18 national people related awards and most recently winning the Nursing Times award for Best UK Employer 2019 we are immensely proud of our achievements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re one of the few NHS organisations across the UK to have achieved a phenomenal 0% nurse vacancy rate within our adult inpatient areas. We have also recently secured over £450m capital funding to transform our sites and give our patients and colleagues within #teamwestherts the working environment they deserve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Hertfordshire Hospitals NHS Trust is one of the largest employers in West Hertfordshire, employing approximately 4500 staff and 450 volunteers. Located within thirty minutes of central London. The trust operates across three sites, Watford General Hospital, where we provide our main emergency care, including a dedicated Paediatric Emergency Department, St Albans City Hospital where we provide a Minor Injuries Unit and Hemel Hempstead Hospital, where we provide an Urgent Care Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
